<div id="main" class="normal-header-enabled">


		
	
    





<div id="content">

<div class="bg-blo">


<h3 style="margin: 0 25%; text-align: center; color: #BDAC81;" >The Alcuin Society is a non-profit organization supported by people who care about the past, present and future of fine books. Founded in 1965, the society is the only organization in Canada dedicated to the entire range of interests relating to books: publishing, book design and production, bookselling, book buying and collecting, printing, binding, papermaking, calligraphy and illustration.</h3>


</div>

<section id="blog" class="default-padding-mod masonry-blog">

<div class="container">

<div class="row">

            

	<div id="post-area" class="masonry-area">
                

		
                

        
                

		<article class="item-blog col-md-4 post-4141 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-alcuin-news category-awards category-book-awards category-book-design" id="post-4141">	

        	<div class="post-container">

			



<div class="post-name">

	<h2 class="entry-title">

		<a href="http://alcuinsociety.com/2019-alcuin-awards-gala-vancouver/" title="2019 Alcuin Awards Gala &#8211; Vancouver"> 2019 Alcuin Awards Gala &#8211; Vancouver</a>

	</h2>

    <div class="entry-meta entry-header">
	<span class="published">January 28, 2019 by Leah Gordon</span>
	<span class="meta-sep"> / </span>
	<span class="comment-count"><span>Comments Off<span class="screen-reader-text"> on 2019 Alcuin Awards Gala &#8211; Vancouver</span></span></span>
    
    </div>
</div>



<div class="entry-content">

    <p>The annual Vancouver Alcuin Awards Event for the 37th Excellence in Book Design in Canada competition will be held on <strong>April 4, 2019</strong> following the book design judging, which will take place on Saturday, March 30. For the first time, the winners of this year&#8217;s awards will not be announced until the awards ceremony, where the winning books will be on display after the announcement of the winners.</p>
<p>The tenth Robert R. Reid Award and Medal for lifetime achievement in the book arts will also be presented at this gala event. This year&#8217;s award will be presented to its winner, <strong>Robert Bringhurst</strong>, who will give a talk for the Society in Vancouver at a later date, to be announced.</p>
<p>A reception will take place following the presentations.</p>
<p>We hope you can attend, especially if you have submitted books to the competition.<em><strong> Reservations are required</strong>, </em>as space is limited; tickets are available at <a href="https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/2019-alcuin-awards-gala-vancouver-tickets-55529661713">EventBrite.</a></p>
<p><strong> Date: Thursday, <span id="OBJ_PREFIX_DWT30_com_zimbra_date" class="Object" role="link">April 4th</span>, 7:00 p.m.<br />
</strong><strong>Place: UBC Robson Square Theatre, 800 Robson Street, Vancouver<br />
</strong><strong> Tickets: Eventbrite<br />
</strong><strong>Cost: Free and open to the public; bring your colleagues and friends!</strong></p>
<p><span id="OBJ_PREFIX_DWT31_ZmEmailObjectHandler" class="Object" role="link"><a href="mailto:awards@alcuinsociety.com?subject=Question%20about%20the%20Alcuin%20Awards%20event%20in%20Vancouver" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a></span> for further information.</p>
<div id="attachment_4145" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img class="wp-image-4145 size-medium" src="http://alcuinsociety.com/content/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/alcuin-award-1-300x150.jpg" alt="Judges: Raphael Daudelin, Frances Hunter, and Mauve Page" width="300" height="150" srcset="http://alcuinsociety.com/content/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/alcuin-award-1-300x150.jpg 300w, http://alcuinsociety.com/content/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/alcuin-award-1-1024x512.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Judges: Raphael Daudelin, Frances Hunter, and Mauve Pagé</p></div>
<p>This free event is sponsored by The Alcuin Society.</p>

