<div class="post-name">

	<h2 class="entry-title">

		<a href="http://alcuinsociety.com/canadian-fine-printing-at-the-university-of-toronto/" title="Canadian Fine Printing at the University of Toronto"> Canadian Fine Printing at the University of Toronto</a>

	</h2>

    <div class="entry-meta entry-header">
	<span class="published">January 19, 2019 by Chester Gryski</span>
	<span class="meta-sep"> / </span>
	<span class="comment-count"><span>Comments Off<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Canadian Fine Printing at the University of Toronto</span></span></span>
    
    </div>
</div>



<div class="entry-content">

    <p>The libraries at the University of Toronto are featuring Canadian Fine Printing. The exhibitions will be launched with an event St Michael’s College on Tuesday, January 22 at 6:00 pm. Details are below.</p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-4130 aligncenter" src="http://alcuinsociety.com/content/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/IMG_7578-3-162x300.jpg" alt="" width="162" height="300" srcset="http://alcuinsociety.com/content/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/IMG_7578-3-162x300.jpg 162w, http://alcuinsociety.com/content/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/IMG_7578-3-554x1024.jpg 554w" sizes="(max-width: 162px) 100vw, 162px" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The libraries are drawing from their own collections for these exhibitions. The work of<strong> Glenn Goluska</strong> will be featured at the John M. Kelly of St. Michael’s College, his College at U of T along with other examples of fine printing. The exhibition at the Robertson Davies Library of Massey College will be devoted exclusively to Goluska.<em>  </em>The E. J. Pratt Library of Victoria College Library and the John W. Graham Library of Trinity College library will also include items of Goluska’s work in their exhibitions along with other examples of fine printing in their collections. The Thomas Fisher Rare Book Library will feature Goluska’s work in a display area of the entrance floor will it readies the main display area for an exhibition entitled <em>Nature on the Page: The Print and Manuscript Culture of Victorian Natural History.</em></p>
<p>The launch will be at 6:00 pm on Tuesday, January 22, 2019 at the Muzzo Family Alumni Hall of St Michael’s College, 121 St Joseph Street, Toronto with a reception to follow at the John M. Kelly Library.</p>
<p>Admission is free but reservations are requested through Eventbrite at<br />
<a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/canadian-fine-press-exhibit-launch-tickets-54536711773">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/canadian-fine-press-exhibit-launch-tickets-54536711773</a></p>
<p> <a href="http://alcuinsociety.com/canadian-fine-printing-at-the-university-of-toronto/#more-4133" class="more-link">Continue Reading&#8230;</a></p>

</div>







