	<h2 class="entry-title">

		<a href="http://alcuinsociety.com/lucie-lambert-a-rare-books-publisher-talks-about-publishing/" title="Lucie Lambert: a rare books publisher talks about publishing"> Lucie Lambert: a rare books publisher talks about publishing</a>

	</h2>

    <div class="entry-meta entry-header">
	<span class="published">January 12, 2019 by Gina Page</span>
	<span class="meta-sep"> / </span>
	<span class="comment-count"><span>Comments Off<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Lucie Lambert: a rare books publisher talks about publishing</span></span></span>
    
    </div>
</div>



<div class="entry-content">

    <p>Lucie Lambert: A rare book publisher talks about publishing &#8212; with focus on the limited edition genre named <em>livre d&#8217;artiste.</em></p>
<div>Date:  <span id="OBJ_PREFIX_DWT19_com_zimbra_date" class="Object" role="link">Thursday, April 11</span>, 2019</div>
<div>Time:  7 pm</div>
<div>Location: The Post at 750 Hamilton Street in the Startup Studio</div>
<div>Please register on<a href="https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/lucie-lambert-a-rare-books-publisher-talks-about-publishing-tickets-54810075411"> Eventbrite.</a></div>
<div></div>
<p><img class="size-medium wp-image-4118 alignleft" src="http://alcuinsociety.com/content/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Lucie-showing-Alphabets-300x225.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="225" srcset="http://alcuinsociety.com/content/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Lucie-showing-Alphabets-300x225.jpg 300w, http://alcuinsociety.com/content/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Lucie-showing-Alphabets-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://alcuinsociety.com/content/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Lucie-showing-Alphabets-400x300.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" />Come meet Lucie Lambert, printmaker, multi-media artist and publisher of livres d&#8217;artiste over half a century, whose books are found in more than fifty distinguished institutions throughout Europe and North America. Her talk will cover the history of livre d&#8217;artiste, the creation of images for her limited edition publications, her association with poets, her collaboration with artisans, and her insights into how these interactions came about and changed her life.</p>

</div>







