	</h2>

    <div class="entry-meta entry-header">
	<span class="published">January 11, 2019 by Grant Hurley</span>
	<span class="meta-sep"> / </span>
	<span class="comment-count"><span>Comments Off<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Call for Entries: Alcuin 2018 Book Design Competition</span></span></span>
    
    </div>
</div>



<div class="entry-content">

    <p><img class="size-medium wp-image-3678 alignleft" src="http://alcuinsociety.com/content/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/AwardsLogo-216x300.png" alt="" width="216" height="300" srcset="http://alcuinsociety.com/content/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/AwardsLogo-216x300.png 216w, http://alcuinsociety.com/content/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/AwardsLogo.png 370w" sizes="(max-width: 216px) 100vw, 216px" />The Alcuin Society will hold its 37th national book design competition, The 2018 Alcuin Society Awards for Excellence in Book Design in Canada, on Saturday, March 30th, 2019, in Vancouver.</p>
<p>To be eligible, a book must have been published in calendar year 2018 by a Canadian publisher and designed by a Canadian designer. There is no limit to the number of titles that may be entered. The entry fee is $40 per title ($30 for Alcuin S<span class="text_exposed_show">ociety members). In addition, we are offering a discount of 20% for 5 or more entries. We encourage submitters to become members; the annual fee is still only $50.</span></p>
